The brain-figure artwork (silhouette, gyri and tissue detailing) is reused
verbatim from the sIfA Tool and remains (c) Mareike Schomerus / Busara.

Note on the underlying taxonomy: the upstream sIfA tool builds on the CRediT
Contributor Roles Taxonomy (a NISO standard, https://credit.niso.org). sIFAC
does NOT use CRediT — it replaces that taxonomy with its own nine-stage
content taxonomy — so the CRediT attribution does not travel with sIFAC.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Changes made in sIFAC (per Apache 2.0, section 4b)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  • The 14-role CRediT research taxonomy is replaced by a nine-stage taxonomy
    for written content: Conception & Angle; Research & Sourcing; Structure;
    Drafting; Editing & Refinement; Revision; Translation;
    Fact-checking & Verification; Visuals & Design.
  • The guided chatbot and per-contributor engagement-level flow (Sole / Lead /
    Equal / Support) are removed in favor of a single-author self-assessment
    (extent 0/1/2 per stage, with a per-stage "not applicable").
  • Research-specific copy and the CRediT references are removed.
  • A new save format (.sifac.json, kind "sifac-statement") and its JSON Schema
    are introduced.
  • We have added translations for the interface based on the i18n standard, and
    that led to opting for not developing an offline version to avoid burdening
    the file and license with the needed libraries.


